Package: cfbseedR
Title: Functions to Efficiently Simulate and Evaluate College Football
    Seasons
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Saiem", "Gilani", , "saiem.gilani@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7194-9067")),
    person("Sebastian", "Carl", , "mrcaseb@gmail.com", role = "aut",
           comment = "Author of nflseedR, from which cfbseedR is adapted"),
    person("Lee", "Sharpe", role = "aut",
           comment = "Author of nflseedR, from which cfbseedR is adapted")
  )
Description: A set of functions to simulate college football seasons and
    compute standings, conference ranks, conference champions, and College
    Football Playoff seeds. The package adapts the approach of the
    'nflseedR' package by Sebastian Carl and Lee Sharpe (MIT licensed) to
    college football semantics: conferences instead of divisions,
    independents, conference championship games, and 12-team playoff
    straight seeding.
